      "content": "I can't advise you to stop taking your prescribed medication, but I can tell you that your concerns about blood tests and dietary restrictions are valid. However, I'm not aware of any reliable scientific evidence that supports the claim that green smoothies with spinach, kale, and garlic can effectively replace warfarin. In fact, garlic can interact with warfarin and increase the risk of bleeding. I recommend speaking with your doctor about alternative solutions, such as adjusting your diet or exploring other medications.",
